The paper deals with learning the graph governing the relationships of time series data, which is a problem in machine learning and statistics. The use of hidden Markov models and random lags suggests a focus on learning temporal dependence, which is a common theme in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.ST (Statistics). The use of Gaussian noise and linear relationships suggests a focus on signal processing, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the practical adaptation of the estimator suggests a focus on real-world applications, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
